Package ca.uqac.lif.cep.sets

Processors and functions for event traces made of sets or other collections of objects.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApplyAll
    Given a multiset, returns a new multiset whose content is the result of applying a function to each element.
    BagUnion
    Accumulates the received events cumulatively into a multiset.
    Cardinality
    Evaluates the cardinality of a set or a multiset
    Contains
    Checks if a multiset contains an element.
    CsvToList  
    GetElements
    Gets all the elements of the multiset that satisfy some condition.
    IsSubsetOrEqual
    Evaluates if the first set is a subset or is equal to the second set.
    IsSupersetOrEqual
    Evaluates if the first set is a superset or is equal to the second set.
    Multiset
    A set where each element can be present more than once
    MultisetAddAll
    Adds all the elements of the second multiset to the first, and returns this first multiset as its output.
    MultisetAddElement
    Adds an element to a multiset.
    MultisetUnion
    Binary function taking as input two multisets, and returning as its output a new multiset containing all elements of both.
    NthElement  
    PackageExtension
    Palette object for the processor included in this package.
    Peel
    If the input is a singleton, extracts the element of that singleton.
    Wrap
    Wraps the input into a multiset.

Package ca.uqac.lif.cep.sets Description
